WEBVTT

00:06.881 --> 00:09.718
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:09.718 --> 00:10.802
[ship horn blares]

00:10.802 --> 00:12.762
<i>Mr. Schrodinger,
welcome back.</i>

00:12.762 --> 00:15.473
- It's been ten years...
- Since you went missing.

00:15.473 --> 00:16.975
How do you know all this?

00:16.975 --> 00:20.061
Anything you want,
just ask Her.

00:20.895 --> 00:23.940
<i>Mathilde is bringing
the Grail to a body of water.</i>

00:23.940 --> 00:25.358
<i>These women in pantsuits,</i>

00:25.358 --> 00:26.609
<i>they're preparing
for some kind of transfer.</i>

00:26.609 --> 00:28.653
You better not be
making trouble, Clara.

00:28.653 --> 00:29.612
[exclaims]

00:30.822 --> 00:32.490
- Where did you get these?
- Mrs. Davis.

00:32.490 --> 00:34.826
This is for
your traveling companion.

00:34.826 --> 00:36.244
<i>Where did you get
those shoes?</i>

00:36.244 --> 00:38.163
I will free you as soon
as you tell me.

00:38.163 --> 00:39.330
This isn't who you are.

00:39.330 --> 00:41.124
Do you want to know
who I really am?

00:43.918 --> 00:46.212
Holy shit!

00:46.212 --> 00:47.380
I need you to do
a favor for me.

00:47.380 --> 00:48.548
What if I say no?

00:48.548 --> 00:49.758
Then you're breaking
your vows.

00:49.758 --> 00:50.884
Is that the pope?

00:50.884 --> 00:52.218
Felipe here has a beef
with your hubby

00:52.218 --> 00:54.804
<i>because he blew him off
for Clara.</i>

00:54.804 --> 00:56.514
<i>Jay never told me
that he knew her.</i>

00:56.514 --> 00:58.350
He just said she was the last
person to have the Grail.

00:58.350 --> 00:59.476
Tell her about the tape.

00:59.476 --> 01:00.894
<i>There's, like,
a mystery tape</i>

01:00.894 --> 01:02.812
<i>that has something to do
with the Holy Grail.</i>

01:02.812 --> 01:04.647
- The red-haired woman?
- Wait for it.

01:06.191 --> 01:08.568
It's a commercial?

01:08.568 --> 01:09.611
What the--

01:11.905 --> 01:14.824
<i>[record player crackling]</i>

01:14.824 --> 01:17.702
<i>[soft ominous music]</i>

01:17.702 --> 01:22.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:22.290 --> 01:24.125
[door creaks open]
[bell dings]

01:24.125 --> 01:25.960
Jay?

01:25.960 --> 01:28.838
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:28.838 --> 01:31.633
[glass crunches]

01:31.633 --> 01:33.093
What the hell?

01:33.093 --> 01:35.887
Hey. What's...

01:35.887 --> 01:39.516
[groaning]

01:40.809 --> 01:43.144
Hey.

01:43.144 --> 01:45.063
Oh, my God.
Did somebody hit you?

01:45.063 --> 01:46.356
Oh, no, no.

01:46.356 --> 01:49.359
- Show me.
- [groaning]

01:49.359 --> 01:51.069
I got into a fight,

01:51.069 --> 01:53.405
which I lost,
because, you know,

01:53.405 --> 01:55.281
- I'm a lover...
- Hey, careful, careful.

01:55.281 --> 01:58.159
Not a fighter. You get it.
[groans]

01:58.159 --> 02:00.912
- Hey, wait. Whoa, whoa.
- [exhales deeply]

02:00.912 --> 02:04.290
Did He do this? The Boss?

02:04.290 --> 02:06.042
It wasn't the Boss, Simone.

02:06.042 --> 02:09.087
I'm okay. I'm okay.

02:09.087 --> 02:11.297
[softly] I'm okay.

02:11.297 --> 02:12.632
Then who was it?

02:12.632 --> 02:14.467
Because I will kick their ass, husband.

02:14.467 --> 02:15.802
- I will kick it good.
- [chuckles]

02:15.802 --> 02:19.264
That's very noble of you, wife,
but I'm okay.

02:19.264 --> 02:21.141
Comes with the territory.
I'm used to it.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.517
"Comes with the territory"?

02:22.517 --> 02:24.644
Who wants to beat up
Jesus Christ?

02:24.644 --> 02:25.854
[laughs]

02:25.854 --> 02:27.856
Ah, I get all kinds in here.

02:27.856 --> 02:30.025
People come to talk.
Some want comfort.

02:30.025 --> 02:31.943
Some just want to kick my ass.

02:31.943 --> 02:36.156
And which kind is Clara?

02:36.156 --> 02:37.657
The red-haired woman who, uh,

02:37.657 --> 02:39.868
was last in possession
of the Holy Grail,

02:39.868 --> 02:41.828
who I've been looking for
this entire time?

02:41.828 --> 02:43.663
You said,
"I think her name is Clara,"

02:43.663 --> 02:45.498
as if you didn't
serve her food right here,

02:45.498 --> 02:46.708
at this very counter.

02:46.708 --> 02:49.711
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:49.711 --> 02:51.296
Who told you?

02:51.296 --> 02:53.006
Uh, Wiley.

02:53.006 --> 02:56.343
Via the Pope.

02:56.343 --> 02:58.595
So what does Clara
come here for?

02:58.595 --> 03:01.890
Ass-kicking? Talk? Comfort?

03:01.890 --> 03:03.266
Simone, I'm sorry.

03:03.266 --> 03:05.518
I already told you,
I can't talk about my other--

03:05.518 --> 03:07.020
The other relationships.
Yeah, I know.

03:07.020 --> 03:09.939
But the thing is, you can talk
about this relationship

03:09.939 --> 03:11.649
because it's in the best
interest of our marriage.

03:11.649 --> 03:13.610
I understand,
but I really can't.

03:13.610 --> 03:15.445
Why, because the Boss is
gonna come out here

03:15.445 --> 03:17.072
and give me a stern talking to?

03:17.072 --> 03:18.365
I'd like to see Him try!

03:18.365 --> 03:20.325
[thunder rumbles loudly]

03:20.325 --> 03:22.369
Can you stop with the thunder?

03:22.369 --> 03:25.080
[groans]
Simone, please, don't do this.

03:25.080 --> 03:26.581
Are you married to her too?

03:26.581 --> 03:27.957
What kind of vows did she take?

03:27.957 --> 03:29.751
You know
I can't talk about this, okay?

03:29.751 --> 03:30.710
Do you love her?

03:30.710 --> 03:33.713
[voice booming]
I love everyone!

03:35.632 --> 03:38.760
[normally]
I love everyone.

03:38.760 --> 03:40.387
[softly] Okay.

03:40.387 --> 03:44.516
I'm sorry.
[breathes shakily]

03:44.516 --> 03:48.395
I didn't mean
to raise my voice.

03:48.395 --> 03:51.272
It's not me.
[sighs]

04:00.365 --> 04:03.785
[life vest squeaking]
[chuckles softly]

04:06.204 --> 04:08.081
[softly]
Excuse me.

04:08.081 --> 04:11.042
[laughs]

04:11.042 --> 04:14.713
I love you, husband.

04:14.713 --> 04:17.632
But I am on the verge
of finding Clara myself,

04:17.632 --> 04:21.302
so if there is something that

04:21.302 --> 04:24.848
you need to tell me
before I do,

04:24.848 --> 04:27.475
now is the time.

04:27.475 --> 04:29.477
Wait, where are you?

04:29.477 --> 04:31.730
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:31.730 --> 04:34.274
I'm going to see a man
about a cat.

04:34.274 --> 04:37.277
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:37.277 --> 04:40.363
[motor rumbling]

04:40.363 --> 04:47.495
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:54.169 --> 04:57.088
<i>[bell tolling]</i>

04:59.758 --> 05:01.760
[waves crashing]
[grunts]

05:01.760 --> 05:04.387
This is where the Algorithm
said he'd be?

05:04.387 --> 05:07.390
<i>[intriguing music]</i>

05:07.390 --> 05:10.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:10.352 --> 05:11.561
That's promising.

05:11.561 --> 05:15.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:15.398 --> 05:16.900
[shouting]

05:16.900 --> 05:18.485
- Oh, fuck me!
- [screams]

05:18.485 --> 05:20.403
I said I didn't want
to be rescued!

05:20.403 --> 05:21.488
- [screams]
- Get away!

05:21.488 --> 05:22.781
- Hey, hey, hey, okay!
- Hey, hey!

05:22.781 --> 05:24.366
Nobody's here to rescue you,
young man.

05:24.366 --> 05:27.327
Put--put the fucking sword
down!

05:27.327 --> 05:29.662
<i>[tense music]</i>

05:29.662 --> 05:32.082
Put--put yours down first.

05:32.082 --> 05:33.166
Same time?

05:33.166 --> 05:39.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:39.339 --> 05:40.590
Oh, God.

05:40.590 --> 05:43.093
Who are you
and why are you here?

05:43.093 --> 05:46.680
We're looking for Clara.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.681
Never heard of her.

05:47.681 --> 05:49.265
No, that's bullshit.

05:49.265 --> 05:51.351
We know you know where she is.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.853
We saw you on the tape.

05:53.853 --> 05:55.355
What tape?

05:55.355 --> 05:57.774
Show him.

06:02.529 --> 06:04.739
[tablet chimes]

06:09.536 --> 06:12.539
"Buns Are the New Guns.

06:12.539 --> 06:15.333
15 Ways to Pump that Rump."

06:15.333 --> 06:16.543
Shit. Wait, what?

06:16.543 --> 06:17.919
Hold--
[scoffs]

06:17.919 --> 06:18.878
Oh, no.

06:18.878 --> 06:22.507
No, no.
That's... something else.

06:24.300 --> 06:26.511
<i>- Is it recording?</i>
- Those are your feet.

06:26.511 --> 06:28.722
<i>Okay, can you point it
at me?</i>

06:28.722 --> 06:29.806
And that is Clara.

06:29.806 --> 06:32.267
<i>Father Hans Ziegler...</i>

06:32.267 --> 06:33.935
And that is your cat.

06:33.935 --> 06:36.771
<i>By now, you understand that
I have in my possession...</i>

06:36.771 --> 06:38.648
You can see,
right here on the collar,

06:38.648 --> 06:40.316
it says, quite adorably,

06:40.316 --> 06:44.070
"Cuddled and cared for
by Dr. Arthur Schrodinger."

06:44.070 --> 06:46.740
Yeah?

06:46.740 --> 06:49.492
That's not my--
[cat meowing]

06:57.792 --> 06:59.919
I can't help. I'm sorry.

06:59.919 --> 07:01.546
Hey. Hey!

07:01.546 --> 07:04.090
Arthur, I am on
a very important quest

07:04.090 --> 07:06.343
to find the Holy Grail
so I can destroy

07:06.343 --> 07:08.136
a dangerously powerful Algorithm,

07:08.136 --> 07:10.013
so powerful,
it knew where you were.

07:10.013 --> 07:12.515
Because apparently--
kay, so you were rescued

07:12.515 --> 07:14.142
and you decided
to come back here?

07:14.142 --> 07:15.935
What--it's not my business.
To each his own.

07:15.935 --> 07:18.563
But if you know Clara--
and hey, I know that you do--

07:18.563 --> 07:20.690
you can help us.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.941
Are you serious? Is he serious?

07:21.941 --> 07:23.443
Yeah, I don't know.
[cat snarls]

07:23.443 --> 07:26.529
But, Lizzie, I think we should
probably forget it, right?

07:26.529 --> 07:29.449
"Lizzie"?

07:29.449 --> 07:32.535
As in short for Elizabeth?

07:32.535 --> 07:36.206
Yeah.

07:36.206 --> 07:38.375
Elizabeth Abbott?

07:38.375 --> 07:41.836
Are you Preston Wiley?

07:41.836 --> 07:43.880
How do you know our names?

07:43.880 --> 07:48.843
I tried to spare you,
but it brought you right to me.

07:48.843 --> 07:50.970
Spare us from--no, no, no.
We don't require sparing.

07:50.970 --> 07:53.348
Just--just tell us
where Clara is,

07:53.348 --> 07:54.808
and we'll be on our way.

07:54.808 --> 07:58.186
She's closer than you think.

07:58.186 --> 08:02.482
But before I tell you
where she is,

08:02.482 --> 08:07.487
you must first understand
who she is.

08:07.487 --> 08:10.699
And that story, her story,

08:10.699 --> 08:13.702
it comes with a warning.

08:13.702 --> 08:17.872
And if you choose to go
through that door,

08:17.872 --> 08:19.791
there will be consequences.

08:19.791 --> 08:23.003
<i>[ominous music]</i>

08:23.003 --> 08:25.338
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:25.338 --> 08:28.216
You sure about this?

08:28.216 --> 08:29.592
Yeah, I'm sure.

08:29.592 --> 08:30.635
Okay.

08:30.635 --> 08:32.303
You stay, I stay.

08:32.303 --> 08:33.972
Okay.

08:36.891 --> 08:39.269
Consequences it is.

08:49.487 --> 08:50.822
Protein.

08:50.822 --> 08:53.241
For the buns.

08:53.241 --> 08:54.951
[crunches]

08:54.951 --> 08:58.371
- Watch out for the--
- [coughs]

08:58.371 --> 08:59.789
Bones.

08:59.789 --> 09:02.208
You okay?

09:02.208 --> 09:03.835
When I first met Clara,

09:03.835 --> 09:06.171
she'd just left
the Sisters of the Coin.

09:06.171 --> 09:07.339
The what?

09:07.339 --> 09:09.632
The Sisters of the Coin.

09:09.632 --> 09:12.344
The top secret organization.

09:12.344 --> 09:15.388
The protectors of the Asset.
The Grail.

09:15.388 --> 09:17.766
The--the banker women.

09:17.766 --> 09:19.309
- Oh, for fuck's sake.
- No, no, no.

09:19.309 --> 09:20.769
- Do you two know anything?
- We do know the banker women.

09:20.769 --> 09:22.020
We know the banker women.
We know the--

09:22.020 --> 09:24.314
[coughing]

09:29.069 --> 09:30.945
How 'bout you just start
from the beginning?

09:33.615 --> 09:36.451
Once upon a time,

09:36.451 --> 09:38.119
there was a young girl

09:38.119 --> 09:42.248
with a head
full of fiery red hair.

09:42.248 --> 09:45.251
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:45.251 --> 09:49.297
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:49.297 --> 09:51.341
[speaking French]

09:51.341 --> 09:58.348
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:04.062 --> 10:06.272
I know it is before her time.

10:06.272 --> 10:08.316
She will not be a bother.

10:08.316 --> 10:09.943
You should get inside.

10:09.943 --> 10:11.820
They are waiting, Mathilde.

10:11.820 --> 10:15.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:15.615 --> 10:16.783
<i>So hang on.</i>

10:16.783 --> 10:19.828
Mathilde, does she also have
red hair,

10:19.828 --> 10:21.830
great skin, wields a knife?

10:21.830 --> 10:22.997
How do you know Mathilde?

10:22.997 --> 10:24.082
Lizzie kicked the shit
out of her.

10:24.082 --> 10:26.543
No, I did not.
I was following her,

10:26.543 --> 10:28.128
and I thought she was Clara.

10:28.128 --> 10:31.297
[chuckles] No.
No, she's not Clara.

10:31.297 --> 10:33.133
<i>But she is...</i>

10:33.133 --> 10:34.217
<i>Maman?</i>

10:35.927 --> 10:38.346
Do not call me <i>maman</i>
when I am at work.

10:38.346 --> 10:41.099
<i>She's her mother?
I did not see that coming.</i>

10:41.099 --> 10:42.183
<i>I did.</i>

10:42.183 --> 10:44.477
<i>Mathilde is Clara's mother,</i>

10:44.477 --> 10:47.939
<i>but she wasn't exactly maternal.</i>

10:47.939 --> 10:50.358
You are going to stay
in this spot, Clara,

10:50.358 --> 10:53.403
and under no circumstances are
you to go through those doors.

10:54.738 --> 10:56.239
[speaks French]

10:59.534 --> 11:01.494
[doors creaking]

11:01.494 --> 11:04.247
<i>Oh, she's definitely
going through those doors.</i>

11:04.247 --> 11:06.291
Yeah, Lizzie here doesn't
respect boundaries either.

11:06.291 --> 11:07.584
It's kind of like
a recurring theme.

11:07.584 --> 11:08.918
A recurring theme?

11:08.918 --> 11:10.879
Oh, you can't help yourself.
Locked doors?

11:10.879 --> 11:12.339
- No.
- Are you kidding me?

11:12.339 --> 11:14.257
I didn't even bother
wrapping her presents.

11:14.257 --> 11:15.884
- [chuckles]
- This one peeks.

11:15.884 --> 11:18.053
'Cause you always gave me
terrible presents.

11:18.053 --> 11:19.554
You didn't hate everything
I gave you.

11:19.554 --> 11:21.097
What are you--

11:21.097 --> 11:22.515
- Yeah, you heard me.
- Stop it.

11:22.515 --> 11:24.309
- [giggles]
- [clears throat]

11:24.309 --> 11:25.435
Sorry.

11:25.435 --> 11:26.811
Please continue.

11:26.811 --> 11:28.688
Thank you.

11:28.688 --> 11:29.939
[tape player clicks]

11:29.939 --> 11:32.025
<i>["Be My Baby"
playing in French]</i>

11:32.025 --> 11:34.069
<i>And while Clara spent
that long summer day</i>

11:34.069 --> 11:37.072
<i>at her mother's work,</i>

11:37.072 --> 11:40.325
<i>she saw some curious things.</i>

11:40.325 --> 11:43.411
- [doors creaking]
<i>- [singing in French]</i>

11:43.411 --> 11:47.082
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:47.082 --> 11:48.708
<i>That woman has
the--the Grail</i>

11:48.708 --> 11:50.043
<i>hidden in her fake belly.</i>

11:50.043 --> 11:51.419
<i>That's what I saw at the lake!</i>

11:51.419 --> 11:52.712
<i>Oh, what,
you get to participate,</i>

11:52.712 --> 11:54.464
- <i>and I have to shut up?
- Both of you just--</i>

11:54.464 --> 11:57.634
I'm trying to describe
the curious things.

11:57.634 --> 11:59.427
Sorry. Go ahead.

11:59.427 --> 12:02.472
[doors creaking]

12:02.472 --> 12:05.433
<i>[singing in French]</i>

12:05.433 --> 12:11.773
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:11.773 --> 12:13.024
<i>Maman?</i>

12:13.024 --> 12:17.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:17.987 --> 12:21.408
<i>Now, Clara could have
called out,</i>

12:21.408 --> 12:23.535
<i>made it known
that she'd been forgotten.</i>

12:23.535 --> 12:26.496
[doors creaking]
<i>But yes, you're right.</i>

12:26.496 --> 12:29.958
<i>She went through
the bloody doors.</i>

12:29.958 --> 12:33.128
<i>And what she saw in there</i>

12:33.128 --> 12:36.965
<i>would change her life forever.</i>

12:36.965 --> 12:39.968
<i>[ominous music]</i>

12:39.968 --> 12:47.142
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:55.817 --> 12:58.153
Why can't you follow
the rules?

12:58.153 --> 13:00.030
I told you not to come in here,
Clara!

13:01.781 --> 13:04.242
[sighs]
Now I must kill you.

13:04.242 --> 13:06.119
- Holy shit!
- Whoa! What?

13:06.119 --> 13:08.163
Whoa, she killed
her own daughter?

13:08.163 --> 13:09.581
- No. Not okay.
- That escalated so quickly.

13:09.581 --> 13:10.874
- No, no, wait. Wait, no.
- Kick the shit out of her--

13:10.874 --> 13:12.709
No--no, she didn't kill her.

13:12.709 --> 13:15.670
But what came next,
what Mathilde was now forced

13:15.670 --> 13:19.632
to subject her daughter to,
was a fate far worse.

13:19.632 --> 13:22.135
I am not a banker, Clara.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.637
I am a Sister of the Coin.

13:27.515 --> 13:30.352
A member of a secret
organization of women

13:30.352 --> 13:32.520
who have worked for centuries

13:32.520 --> 13:34.647
in financial institutions
as a means

13:34.647 --> 13:36.524
to hide our true agenda,

13:36.524 --> 13:41.905
the care and protection
of the Asset.

13:43.073 --> 13:45.909
The Asset came to us
millennia ago,

13:45.909 --> 13:48.286
when two apostles
of the Christ,

13:48.286 --> 13:51.498
each claiming it as their own,
they dueled...

13:51.498 --> 13:53.416
<i>[swords clashing]</i>
Resulting in both their deaths.

13:53.416 --> 13:55.293
<i>[men screaming]</i>
And so the asset

13:55.293 --> 13:58.213
was held in trust
by their widows.

13:58.213 --> 14:00.965
These would become
the first Sisters,

14:00.965 --> 14:04.052
bankers tasked with
looking after the Asset.

14:04.052 --> 14:06.304
But it is just a bowl.

14:06.304 --> 14:08.306
Why does it need looking after?

14:08.306 --> 14:12.644
Because, Clara,
it is not just a bowl.

14:12.644 --> 14:15.105
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:15.105 --> 14:17.232
It has a temper.

14:17.232 --> 14:21.027
If it's not properly cared for,

14:21.027 --> 14:23.863
bad things happen.
<i>[crowd screaming]</i>

14:23.863 --> 14:28.034
<i>So the Grail was responsible
for the eruption of Pompeii?</i>

14:28.034 --> 14:30.412
Well, the Sisters
certainly believe so.

14:30.412 --> 14:34.582
The Grail was apparently nearby
when the tragedy occurred,

14:34.582 --> 14:37.836
which is why they developed
the Articles of Care,

14:37.836 --> 14:41.589
rules that they must follow
to keep the bowl appeased.

14:41.589 --> 14:43.883
So they treat a bowl
like a baby?

14:43.883 --> 14:45.343
They're its mothers.

14:45.343 --> 14:47.095
Exactly.

14:47.095 --> 14:48.888
And the Sisters believed

14:48.888 --> 14:50.306
that if they didn't
follow the rules,

14:50.306 --> 14:51.975
there'd be
adverse consequences.

14:51.975 --> 14:56.438
So if the Grail wasn't kept
in a state of perpetual motion,

14:56.438 --> 15:00.191
for example,
it would emit a foul odor.

15:00.191 --> 15:03.194
Ah, so the baby Grail
gets fussy,

15:03.194 --> 15:04.821
you gotta take it
for a drive in the car

15:04.821 --> 15:06.072
so it doesn't make a boom-boom.

15:06.072 --> 15:07.449
Don't mock the rules, boy,

15:07.449 --> 15:10.744
especially not the most
important rule of all.

15:10.744 --> 15:14.372
Thou shall not sip.

15:14.372 --> 15:16.583
Why do you do this, <i>Maman?</i>

15:16.583 --> 15:19.669
Why did you care so much
about that bowl?

15:19.669 --> 15:24.382
Because I took a vow,
as my <i>maman</i> did before me,

15:24.382 --> 15:26.634
and because I said I would.

15:26.634 --> 15:28.303
[sighs]

15:28.303 --> 15:30.180
You are not cut out
to be a Sister, Clara,

15:30.180 --> 15:31.431
for to be in service
of the Asset

15:31.431 --> 15:33.641
is to do whatever it takes.

15:37.020 --> 15:38.146
[sighs]

15:38.146 --> 15:40.023
But now that you've seen
all this,

15:40.023 --> 15:42.484
and I would rather not
kill you,

15:42.484 --> 15:45.487
I have no choice but to begin
your training.

15:45.487 --> 15:48.031
You will study
the Articles of Care,

15:48.031 --> 15:50.950
and you will learn
how to execute them,

15:50.950 --> 15:53.578
though I doubt you will be
any good.

15:53.578 --> 15:55.830
Then I vow

15:55.830 --> 15:58.291
to prove you wrong, <i>Maman,</i>

15:58.291 --> 16:02.420
whatever it takes.

16:04.255 --> 16:06.216
Clara spent
the next several years

16:06.216 --> 16:07.509
at a special academy,

16:07.509 --> 16:10.929
training to become
the most capable sister.

16:10.929 --> 16:12.889
A special academy.
That's cool.

16:12.889 --> 16:14.265
Kinda like Grail Hogwarts.

16:14.265 --> 16:16.184
Yeah, no offense,
but can we just fast-forward

16:16.184 --> 16:17.143
to the part
where we're talking about

16:17.143 --> 16:18.978
the sneaker commercial, please?

16:18.978 --> 16:20.897
Very well.

16:20.897 --> 16:22.023
Right you are.

16:22.023 --> 16:25.026
all: As the skies rain fire,

16:25.026 --> 16:27.445
the Sisters must acquire

16:27.445 --> 16:30.657
and invest with mind and heart

16:30.657 --> 16:33.243
and never, ever part

16:33.243 --> 16:36.204
with that which we all serve,

16:36.204 --> 16:37.914
the Asset.

16:37.914 --> 16:40.041
And what, Sisters,

16:40.041 --> 16:43.878
is the most inviolable?

16:43.878 --> 16:48.091
all: Thou shall not sip.

16:51.177 --> 16:54.389
Before we begin
our quarterly earnings,

16:54.389 --> 16:59.227
Sister Mathilde would like
to make a proposal.

17:00.270 --> 17:01.855
As you are all well aware,

17:01.855 --> 17:04.441
Article 13
of the Articles of Care states

17:04.441 --> 17:07.277
the asset must be looked upon
by no less than 1%

17:07.277 --> 17:09.320
of the global population annually,

17:09.320 --> 17:13.199
lest the skies rain fire,
et cetera, et cetera.

17:13.199 --> 17:15.910
But the world's population
has exploded,

17:15.910 --> 17:20.498
and now we must guarantee
75 million individuals

17:20.498 --> 17:22.751
lay eyes upon it
in a single year.

17:22.751 --> 17:27.172
And still, we transport
the Asset all over the world

17:27.172 --> 17:29.424
to hit our quota.

17:29.424 --> 17:32.344
Yet what if I told you

17:32.344 --> 17:36.348
we could capture
those 75 million viewers

17:36.348 --> 17:39.851
in a single minute,
all at once?

17:39.851 --> 17:42.645
[excited whispering]

17:42.645 --> 17:45.315
Balderdash.

17:45.315 --> 17:46.941
No, Sister.

17:46.941 --> 17:48.860
Not balderdash.

17:48.860 --> 17:51.237
<i>[intriguing music]</i>

17:51.237 --> 17:55.742
A Super Bowl commercial,

17:55.742 --> 17:58.453
Which will not only be seen
at the Super Bowl,

17:58.453 --> 18:01.414
but for months,
maybe even years to come,

18:01.414 --> 18:03.625
broadcast around the world

18:03.625 --> 18:07.629
with the kind of reach
we could only dream of.

18:07.629 --> 18:10.131
We will camouflage
the presence of the Asset

18:10.131 --> 18:11.716
within the ad itself.

18:11.716 --> 18:16.846
And to do so, I have identified
a brand with mass appeal,

18:16.846 --> 18:19.849
the coolest athletic shoe
in the world,

18:19.849 --> 18:22.560
one destined to reach
iconic status

18:22.560 --> 18:25.313
and only gain in popularity:

18:25.313 --> 18:28.441
British Knights.

18:28.441 --> 18:30.360
[snaps]
Apron man!

18:32.237 --> 18:34.489
We open
in 14th-century France,

18:34.489 --> 18:36.825
a dramatic execution,

18:36.825 --> 18:39.536
as Knights Templar
burn at the stake

18:39.536 --> 18:41.287
under the torches of French--

18:41.287 --> 18:42.831
Yeah, no.
We--we saw the commercial.

18:42.831 --> 18:45.041
We don't need to hear
the whole pitch, man.

18:45.041 --> 18:46.334
Yeah.
What I want to know is...

18:46.334 --> 18:48.628
Who's going to pay for this?

18:48.628 --> 18:51.256
Our most loyal apron man, Hans.

18:51.256 --> 18:55.176
[crowd gasps]

18:55.176 --> 18:56.845
- Me?
- Yes, Hans.

18:56.845 --> 19:00.473
You will secure what we need
to make this commercial

19:00.473 --> 19:02.851
by infiltrating the Vatican

19:02.851 --> 19:05.562
and becoming a priest.

19:05.562 --> 19:08.857
Father Ziegler has
a nice ring to it, no?

19:08.857 --> 19:13.737
both: Oh!

19:13.737 --> 19:18.199
I would do anything for...
the Sisterhood,

19:18.199 --> 19:19.701
but why the Vatican?

19:19.701 --> 19:21.619
Because those <i>putain de cons</i>
don't allow women

19:21.619 --> 19:23.830
to hold positions of power
within the church.

19:23.830 --> 19:26.207
Besides, the Vatican owns
so much land,

19:26.207 --> 19:27.542
they will not notice

19:27.542 --> 19:29.711
when you find the perfect
location for our shoot

19:29.711 --> 19:32.547
nor when you embezzle the funds
to subsidize our budget.

19:32.547 --> 19:36.718
You want me to become
a priest so I can steal?

19:36.718 --> 19:40.555
I want you to be quiet
and do as you're told.

19:41.973 --> 19:44.142
Is that you, Mathilde,

19:44.142 --> 19:47.020
featured in your own
commercial?

19:47.020 --> 19:51.066
In order to ensure
the security of the Asset,

19:51.066 --> 19:53.360
I must write, direct,

19:53.360 --> 19:57.072
and star in the ad myself.

19:57.072 --> 19:59.157
You're too old.

19:59.157 --> 20:00.742
[laughter]

20:00.742 --> 20:04.079
If these British Knights are
as cool as you say,

20:04.079 --> 20:05.789
the hero needs to be youthful.

20:05.789 --> 20:10.251
We are not trying
to sell sneakers, okay?

20:10.251 --> 20:11.419
- It is only a method--
<i>- Pardon.</i>

20:11.419 --> 20:15.674
[excited murmuring]

20:15.674 --> 20:18.802
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

20:18.802 --> 20:20.261
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:20.261 --> 20:22.430
I'll do it.

20:22.430 --> 20:25.350
You will not.

20:25.350 --> 20:26.768
I am young.

20:26.768 --> 20:29.896
I can be trusted
to handle the Asset,

20:29.896 --> 20:33.566
and this will free you to focus
on your work behind the camera.

20:33.566 --> 20:35.902
Well, that settles it.

20:35.902 --> 20:39.572
Mathilde,
if you want our approval,

20:39.572 --> 20:41.241
Clara will be the star.

20:41.241 --> 20:44.244
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:44.244 --> 20:48.373
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:48.373 --> 20:49.958
All in favor?

20:49.958 --> 20:56.923
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:59.175 --> 21:00.927
Tails have it.

21:00.927 --> 21:03.013
The commercial proceeds.

21:03.013 --> 21:06.016
[applause]

21:06.016 --> 21:13.023
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:25.493 --> 21:28.455
[indistinct chatter]

21:28.455 --> 21:31.374
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

21:31.374 --> 21:36.963
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:36.963 --> 21:38.173
<i>Merci.</i>

21:40.592 --> 21:42.594
<i>Va-t'en!</i> I'm busy.

21:42.594 --> 21:46.723
<i>Maman,</i>
I need to speak with you.

21:46.723 --> 21:49.768
I have some questions about--

21:51.686 --> 21:54.064
Move aside.

21:59.069 --> 22:03.198
[clears throat]
Um, <i>Maman,</i> it's really--

22:03.198 --> 22:05.658
two seconds.

22:05.658 --> 22:07.035
I'm very busy, Clara.

22:07.035 --> 22:08.787
I do not have time
to babysit you.

22:10.705 --> 22:12.749
<i>[ominous music]</i>

22:12.749 --> 22:16.419
Always on the outside
looking in.

22:16.419 --> 22:17.962
Excuse me?

22:17.962 --> 22:20.006
Surely you remember
your mother's apron man.

22:20.006 --> 22:23.927
15 years of servitude should
not be that easily forgotten.

22:23.927 --> 22:26.262
Hans?

22:26.262 --> 22:27.722
Yes, of course.

22:27.722 --> 22:30.767
It's been a while,
and I didn't recognize you in--

22:30.767 --> 22:33.103
The fruits of my labor.

22:33.103 --> 22:35.021
When your mother sent me off
to the Vatican

22:35.021 --> 22:36.231
to do her bidding,

22:36.231 --> 22:39.901
I was at first resentful.

22:39.901 --> 22:41.736
But now I understand
it was a necessary step

22:41.736 --> 22:43.279
in realizing my potential.

22:43.279 --> 22:47.575
You see, life is full of doors,
just like this one.

22:48.660 --> 22:50.995
And there are
two kinds of people,

22:50.995 --> 22:52.747
those outside

22:52.747 --> 22:54.582
and those on the inside.

22:57.043 --> 22:58.670
All right.

23:02.090 --> 23:03.967
Hans, what are you doing
standing there?

23:03.967 --> 23:05.468
Take off
that ridiculous costume.

23:05.468 --> 23:06.594
Fetch me tea.

23:06.594 --> 23:09.305
It is not a costume.

23:09.305 --> 23:12.684
Now, Hans.

23:12.684 --> 23:15.061
Of course, ma'am.
Right away, ma'am.

23:17.439 --> 23:19.607
It is always those
closest to us

23:19.607 --> 23:22.444
whose blades cut deepest, no?

23:22.444 --> 23:27.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:27.323 --> 23:28.658
Cut!

23:28.658 --> 23:31.036
[bell rings]

23:31.036 --> 23:33.121
[speaking French]

23:33.121 --> 23:34.539
Where's the intensity?

23:34.539 --> 23:36.499
You're not giving me
what I need, Clara.

23:36.499 --> 23:37.834
I'm doing my best, <i>Maman.</i>

23:37.834 --> 23:40.503
Well, your best
is not good enough.

23:40.503 --> 23:42.339
[sniffs]

23:42.339 --> 23:44.132
What's that awful smell?

23:44.132 --> 23:46.968
Perhaps it's my daughter's
terrible performance.

23:46.968 --> 23:48.511
[beeping]

23:48.511 --> 23:49.888
Psst, psst!

23:54.225 --> 23:55.810
Oh, well, great.

23:55.810 --> 23:58.396
Now you've upset the Asset.

23:58.396 --> 23:59.898
Clear the set!

23:59.898 --> 24:03.360
I must clear my head.
Terrible headache.

24:03.360 --> 24:09.574
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:09.574 --> 24:11.659
Meet me at sundown.

24:14.371 --> 24:18.041
<i>Oh, the old "meet me
at sundown" cryptic note.</i>

24:18.041 --> 24:20.210
It's a classic,
and it's good to know

24:20.210 --> 24:23.380
our boy Hans has always been
a cliché, shady fuck,

24:23.380 --> 24:25.465
But do you think he helped
Clara steal the Grail?

24:25.465 --> 24:29.719
Would you two prefer
to keep on wildly theorizing,

24:29.719 --> 24:31.763
or can I carry on
with the story?

24:31.763 --> 24:33.264
By all means.

24:33.264 --> 24:36.267
[door creaks, slams]

24:36.267 --> 24:39.229
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:39.229 --> 24:46.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:57.247 --> 24:59.374
Top row,
fourth from the left.

25:08.717 --> 25:11.678
<i>[mystical ringing]</i>

25:11.678 --> 25:16.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:16.850 --> 25:18.268
How did you get this?

25:18.268 --> 25:20.061
Oh, I did not get it.

25:20.061 --> 25:21.938
I made it.

25:21.938 --> 25:25.483
This decoy was manufactured
to my exact specifications

25:25.483 --> 25:26.943
by a blind craftsman

25:26.943 --> 25:28.945
and is indistinguishable
from the original.

25:28.945 --> 25:30.280
What will you do with this?

25:30.280 --> 25:32.157
Oh, I will not do anything
with it, Clara.

25:32.157 --> 25:35.827
You are the only one permitted
to handle the actual Grail,

25:35.827 --> 25:38.747
so you will replace it
with this decoy

25:38.747 --> 25:40.081
and bring me the real thing.

25:40.081 --> 25:42.083
Why would I do that for you?

25:44.210 --> 25:47.422
It is not just for me, Clara.

25:47.422 --> 25:49.257
It is for both of us.

25:49.257 --> 25:52.177
All we've ever wanted was
Mathilde's approval,

25:52.177 --> 25:55.263
but she can never give it to us
because of that accursed bowl.

25:55.263 --> 25:57.974
The Grail is an object
of immense power.

25:57.974 --> 26:00.935
Many have tried to destroy it
over the centuries,

26:00.935 --> 26:04.481
but only the Vatican has
the resources to obliterate it

26:04.481 --> 26:06.191
once and for all.

26:06.191 --> 26:08.151
In doing so,

26:08.151 --> 26:09.944
it would free Mathilde
and all the Sisters

26:09.944 --> 26:11.321
from the burden
of caring for it.

26:11.321 --> 26:15.200
Then, Clara,

26:15.200 --> 26:18.703
we could finally both get
the affection we deserve.

26:28.046 --> 26:30.048
Give me one reason
to trust you.

26:32.717 --> 26:37.514
Because, Clara,

26:37.514 --> 26:39.182
I'm your father.

26:39.182 --> 26:42.936
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:42.936 --> 26:44.688
I fucking knew it!

26:44.688 --> 26:45.897
Why don't you tell
the story, then?

26:45.897 --> 26:47.065
- No, no, no, no, no.
- I'm so--

26:47.065 --> 26:48.817
He's doing great.

26:48.817 --> 26:50.068
You're doing great.

26:51.903 --> 26:53.238
You lie.

26:53.238 --> 26:55.907
My mother would never bend
the rule

26:55.907 --> 26:57.951
to consummate
with an apron man.

26:57.951 --> 27:00.704
And if you believe
I am just as reckless

27:00.704 --> 27:02.497
to break my vow
to the Sisterhood,

27:02.497 --> 27:04.791
then you are dead wrong.

27:04.791 --> 27:07.085
If I see you
anywhere near the Asset

27:07.085 --> 27:08.503
with your little decoy,

27:08.503 --> 27:11.589
I will not hesitate
to take your head off.

27:11.589 --> 27:13.717
And you should know,

27:13.717 --> 27:16.386
I've been practicing.

27:16.386 --> 27:20.515
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:25.061 --> 27:26.604
[shouting in French]

27:26.604 --> 27:29.607
[all shouting]

27:29.607 --> 27:32.736
<i>[funky music]</i>

27:32.736 --> 27:37.073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:37.073 --> 27:38.742
Okay, here we go.

27:38.742 --> 27:40.452
[bell rings]

27:40.452 --> 27:42.495
Action!

27:42.495 --> 27:44.289
[speaking French]

27:52.881 --> 27:55.967
[speaking French]

28:00.388 --> 28:01.514
Cut!

28:01.514 --> 28:02.766
[bell rings]

28:02.766 --> 28:04.267
From the top.

28:04.267 --> 28:05.352
Action!

28:06.770 --> 28:07.896
Cut!

28:08.396 --> 28:09.564
Cut!

28:09.564 --> 28:11.066
- Cut!
- Back to one.

28:11.066 --> 28:12.442
My God. From the top.

28:16.112 --> 28:18.948
No, no, no, no, no!
[groans]

28:18.948 --> 28:20.700
I still don't believe you.
[speaking French]

28:20.700 --> 28:23.995
How are you so incapable
of showing genuine emotion?

28:23.995 --> 28:25.413
You care for this woman.

28:25.413 --> 28:27.123
Why do you refuse
to nurture her

28:27.123 --> 28:28.291
in the last moments of life?

28:28.291 --> 28:30.210
[speaking French]
Who are you

28:30.210 --> 28:32.295
to lecture me about nurturing?

28:32.295 --> 28:34.839
[groans]

28:34.839 --> 28:37.217
Clear the set.

28:37.217 --> 28:38.635
Everyone.

28:38.635 --> 28:40.387
Except you.

28:42.222 --> 28:43.556
I think you're doing
a wonderful job.

28:43.556 --> 28:46.142
[speaking French]

28:52.857 --> 28:55.735
[murmuring in French]

28:55.735 --> 29:00.657
I'm not sure how much more
of this I can take.

29:00.657 --> 29:03.785
I have my limits.

29:03.785 --> 29:05.537
I really do.

29:13.712 --> 29:15.380
I'm dying.

29:16.673 --> 29:18.133
What?

29:22.095 --> 29:27.017
I've been, um,
getting these headaches.

29:27.017 --> 29:31.271
So, um, I went to a doctor,

29:31.271 --> 29:36.151
a specialist, who ran tests.

29:36.151 --> 29:38.737
Unfortunately,
the results were...

29:38.737 --> 29:42.449
<i>[somber music]</i>

29:42.449 --> 29:46.453
Well, there isn't much
they can do.

29:46.453 --> 29:51.916
My situation has
forced me to...

29:51.916 --> 29:55.503
reflect upon my duty

29:55.503 --> 29:59.049
and my legacy.

29:59.049 --> 30:01.551
You are my legacy, Clara.

30:01.551 --> 30:08.516
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:12.937 --> 30:16.024
[breathing shakily]

30:19.194 --> 30:20.653
Do you need a moment?

30:24.032 --> 30:26.076
No.

30:26.076 --> 30:27.285
Let's shoot.

30:29.037 --> 30:31.998
Let's shoot.

30:31.998 --> 30:34.334
And action!

30:58.775 --> 31:03.029
[sniffling]

31:03.029 --> 31:04.364
All right, good enough.

31:04.364 --> 31:06.700
Uh, moving on.
[bell rings]

31:06.700 --> 31:09.494
[crying]

31:10.912 --> 31:14.457
Um, let's go to...

31:16.209 --> 31:18.837
Clara, this platform
that we built

31:18.837 --> 31:21.131
runs just under the water.

31:21.131 --> 31:24.634
So all you're gonna do
is run here.

31:24.634 --> 31:27.220
But past this point,
you'll be going for a swim.

31:27.220 --> 31:28.346
Any questions?

31:28.346 --> 31:31.307
No. I'm--I'm good to go.

31:31.307 --> 31:32.934
[speaking French]
Positions, everyone!

31:32.934 --> 31:35.186
Top, top, top, top, top!

31:36.688 --> 31:37.897
Where is it?

31:37.897 --> 31:39.441
Where is what?

31:39.441 --> 31:41.484
The decoy I offered you,
it's gone.

31:41.484 --> 31:43.737
And you are the only one
who knew where it was hidden.

31:43.737 --> 31:46.031
Why would I take your decoy?

31:46.031 --> 31:48.283
I am a loyal
Sister of the Coin.

31:48.283 --> 31:51.036
But if you feel that some
of your property was stolen,

31:51.036 --> 31:54.330
you should report it
to security immediately.

31:54.330 --> 31:55.832
Give it back to me, now!

31:55.832 --> 31:57.292
Hey, Hans!

31:57.292 --> 32:01.546
Stop distracting my actor
and get me a tea, Earl Grey.

32:01.546 --> 32:02.547
Get it yourself!

32:02.547 --> 32:04.549
[crowd gasps]

32:04.549 --> 32:08.511
<i>[dark music]</i>

32:08.511 --> 32:10.180
<i>Quoi?</i>

32:13.224 --> 32:17.062
I am the one who made
all of this possible!

32:17.062 --> 32:18.938
I spent years at the Vatican,

32:18.938 --> 32:22.317
shifting money around so you
could fund this production.

32:22.317 --> 32:23.735
I am the one
who found this place

32:23.735 --> 32:25.862
in their secret holdings,
and what thanks do I get,

32:25.862 --> 32:27.197
to be your errand boy?

32:27.197 --> 32:29.783
No, I am a priest now,

32:29.783 --> 32:31.409
and I am going back
to where I'm given

32:31.409 --> 32:33.578
the respect I deserve.

32:35.997 --> 32:37.874
Security.

32:37.874 --> 32:39.709
[stammering]

32:39.709 --> 32:41.544
I don't know what you're doing,
but once you do it,

32:41.544 --> 32:43.713
I will come after you with
the full power of the Vatican.

32:43.713 --> 32:45.840
I vow it!

32:45.840 --> 32:47.759
Leave me be!

32:50.387 --> 32:51.930
Back to work, people!

32:51.930 --> 32:54.015
We're losing light!

32:54.015 --> 32:56.142
[horse neighs]

32:56.142 --> 32:57.727
<i>Merci.</i>

32:57.727 --> 33:00.647
[indistinct chatter]

33:03.692 --> 33:05.276
Quiet on set.

33:05.276 --> 33:07.445
Clara, are you ready?

33:09.114 --> 33:11.616
Roll camera.

33:11.616 --> 33:13.827
Three, two, one.

33:13.827 --> 33:17.122
And action!

33:17.122 --> 33:18.665
[shouts]

33:18.665 --> 33:21.668
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

33:21.668 --> 33:28.341
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:34.973 --> 33:35.974
Cut!

33:35.974 --> 33:41.813
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:47.986 --> 33:50.780
[water burbling]

33:53.950 --> 33:56.870
<i>[dramatic choral music]</i>

33:56.870 --> 33:58.246
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:58.246 --> 34:00.790
[sighs]

34:00.790 --> 34:03.585
[clapping]

34:03.585 --> 34:05.295
We're good.
[sighs]

34:05.295 --> 34:06.546
We got it. That's a wrap.

34:06.546 --> 34:09.257
Ah!
[applause]

34:09.257 --> 34:15.513
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:21.853 --> 34:24.564
She swapped the Grail out
for the decoy underwater,

34:24.564 --> 34:26.107
- didn't she?
- Of course she did.

34:26.107 --> 34:30.278
You two are simply incapable
of listening, aren't you?

34:32.489 --> 34:36.493
And so after 26 days,

34:36.493 --> 34:39.204
three major injuries,
two production designers,

34:39.204 --> 34:41.498
and $18 million

34:41.498 --> 34:43.458
- of the Vatican's money...
- Wow.

34:43.458 --> 34:46.294
Mathilde and the Sisters
of the Coin completed

34:46.294 --> 34:50.423
the most ambitious commercial
in history.

34:53.218 --> 34:54.719
Yes.

34:54.719 --> 34:56.304
How come
no one's ever seen it?

34:56.304 --> 34:58.056
Oh.

34:58.056 --> 35:01.226
Well, isn't it obvious?

35:01.226 --> 35:02.894
No.

35:02.894 --> 35:04.938
No?

35:04.938 --> 35:06.398
Shall I tell you?

35:07.857 --> 35:09.484
We want to know.

35:19.536 --> 35:22.455
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

35:22.455 --> 35:29.629
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:31.589 --> 35:34.759
<i>[funky music]</i>

35:34.759 --> 35:38.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:38.930 --> 35:42.517
<i>Sometimes,
at the end of the road,</i>

35:42.517 --> 35:45.562
<i>when all seems lost,</i>

35:45.562 --> 35:48.106
<i>miracles happen.</i>

35:48.106 --> 35:50.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:52.318 --> 35:55.447
[crowd murmuring]

35:59.784 --> 36:02.996
That was very... impressive.

36:02.996 --> 36:06.624
But I'm a bit confused.

36:06.624 --> 36:08.126
What's confusing?

36:08.126 --> 36:09.461
I have delivered

36:09.461 --> 36:11.796
British Knights Corporation
a masterpiece,

36:11.796 --> 36:15.300
and all you have to do is
air it during the Super Bowl.

36:15.300 --> 36:16.426
But here's the thing.

36:16.426 --> 36:18.053
We didn't hire you to do this.

36:18.053 --> 36:20.805
We just met you
for the first time today.

36:20.805 --> 36:22.974
Yes, but I spoke to someone
in your office.

36:22.974 --> 36:25.852
He was incredibly enthusiastic
about the prospect.

36:25.852 --> 36:28.688
His name, I believe, was Brian.

36:31.232 --> 36:34.361
[indistinct murmuring]

36:39.949 --> 36:41.242
Brian's an intern.

36:41.242 --> 36:43.953
[crowd groaning]

36:45.663 --> 36:48.958
But I've put my heart
into this.

36:48.958 --> 36:51.503
And I give you this.
It's a gift. It's for free.

36:51.503 --> 36:53.546
I'm sorry. It's a pass.

36:53.546 --> 36:56.966
[crowd gasps]

36:56.966 --> 36:59.552
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

36:59.552 --> 37:05.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:05.266 --> 37:09.312
You didn't get
their permission?

37:09.312 --> 37:12.148
If I asked for permission
every time in my life--

37:12.148 --> 37:14.693
Spare us, Mathilde.

37:14.693 --> 37:19.030
Your folly has cost us dearly.

37:19.030 --> 37:23.451
And not a single eye will
fall upon the Asset,

37:23.451 --> 37:25.286
which means we will
have to triple

37:25.286 --> 37:26.955
our efforts to have it seen.

37:26.955 --> 37:31.126
[all muttering]

37:31.126 --> 37:33.962
This never happened.

37:33.962 --> 37:38.008
Bury every goddamn shoe.

37:38.008 --> 37:40.844
And if the world ever sees
a frame

37:40.844 --> 37:44.681
of this ludicrous endeavor,

37:44.681 --> 37:50.103
I will see that you are
banished from the Sisterhood.

37:50.103 --> 37:57.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:10.623 --> 38:12.709
You cut my line.

38:17.130 --> 38:18.548
I didn't believe you.

38:18.548 --> 38:20.967
Yet I believed you.

38:23.762 --> 38:27.098
You're not really dying,
are you?

38:27.098 --> 38:29.517
Whatever it takes.

38:29.517 --> 38:36.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:46.326 --> 38:47.452
My resignation.

38:47.452 --> 38:50.413
<i>[music darkens]</i>

38:50.413 --> 38:52.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:52.540 --> 38:55.293
I do not accept it.

38:55.293 --> 38:57.754
You're fired, Clara.

38:57.754 --> 39:00.799
Leave, and never show
your face here again.

39:03.009 --> 39:07.806
Out of my love
and dedication to you,

39:07.806 --> 39:11.017
I vow it will be done.

39:11.017 --> 39:15.146
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:15.146 --> 39:16.648
Goodbye, <i>Maman.</i>

39:16.648 --> 39:23.822
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:23.822 --> 39:26.700
<i>So she swapped the Grail
to fuck over her mom,</i>

39:26.700 --> 39:28.660
but her mom didn't know
she swapped it,

39:28.660 --> 39:32.330
so why bother fucking with her
at all?

39:32.330 --> 39:33.373
Ooh, right.

39:33.373 --> 39:34.749
- Mom stuff.
- Hmm?

39:34.749 --> 39:36.167
Lizzie's mom shot her
with a crossbow.

39:36.167 --> 39:37.460
She's still kinda
working through it.

39:37.460 --> 39:38.420
All right, all right,
all right,

39:38.420 --> 39:39.504
I don't want to talk about me.

39:39.504 --> 39:42.007
When do you come in
to this story?

39:42.007 --> 39:44.092
[cat meows]

39:44.092 --> 39:46.302
Ah, yes.

39:46.302 --> 39:51.349
It is indeed time for Apollo
and I to enter stage right.

39:51.349 --> 39:54.352
<i>[intriguing music]</i>

39:54.352 --> 40:01.317
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:02.819 --> 40:04.571
[footsteps approaching]

40:08.658 --> 40:10.118
Uh, oh, office hours are over.

40:10.118 --> 40:13.246
You'll have to come back
tomorrow, I'm afraid.

40:13.246 --> 40:15.331
Um...

40:15.331 --> 40:18.376
I'm not one of your students, Professor.

40:18.376 --> 40:20.920
My name is Clara.

40:20.920 --> 40:24.257
I am, um,
Mathilde La Fleur's daughter.

40:26.051 --> 40:27.886
And, uh,

40:27.886 --> 40:30.889
I am also your daughter.

40:30.889 --> 40:33.391
- I knew it!
- [screams] What the fuck?

40:33.391 --> 40:34.559
- I knew it.
- What?

40:34.559 --> 40:35.894
- You did not know it.
- I knew it.

40:35.894 --> 40:37.645
You said you knew that
the priest was the father.

40:37.645 --> 40:39.147
- I knew that too.
- He did not know it.

40:39.147 --> 40:42.901
I also knew
that the priest was lying

40:42.901 --> 40:46.905
because, you know, Beardo here
is her true father.

40:46.905 --> 40:48.948
I can't believe
you're her father.

40:48.948 --> 40:50.909
Yeah. I mean, I can, but--

40:50.909 --> 40:53.411
Yeah, well,
I didn't bloody well know it

40:53.411 --> 40:54.954
at the time, did I, right?

40:54.954 --> 40:57.791
And trust me,
it was quite the development.

40:57.791 --> 41:00.710
How did Clara even know
where you were?

41:01.753 --> 41:03.922
I found your letters.

41:03.922 --> 41:06.508
My mother kept them hidden,

41:06.508 --> 41:09.761
but I found them
when I was a child.

41:09.761 --> 41:12.806
I suspect she never told you
about me.

41:14.641 --> 41:16.393
She didn't.

41:16.393 --> 41:17.936
Don't take it personally.

41:17.936 --> 41:20.313
It was reckless of her
to have a relationship

41:20.313 --> 41:22.107
with an outsider.

41:22.107 --> 41:24.484
It's forbidden
by the Sisterhood.

41:24.484 --> 41:26.069
The Sisterhood?

41:26.069 --> 41:28.863
The Sisters of the Coin.

41:28.863 --> 41:31.533
- They are a...
<i>- Secret organization</i>

41:31.533 --> 41:33.451
sworn to protect the Asset.

41:33.451 --> 41:35.745
See? We're paying attention.

41:35.745 --> 41:37.706
Why did she come to you,
Arthur?

41:37.706 --> 41:40.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:40.000 --> 41:43.044
Because I'm a scientist.

41:43.044 --> 41:45.880
If you loved my mother as
much as you letters suggested,

41:45.880 --> 41:48.049
you deserve to know
why she disappeared.

41:48.049 --> 41:51.970
She is incapable
of loving anyone,

41:51.970 --> 41:55.223
not as long as this exists.

41:55.223 --> 41:58.685
Ah.

41:58.685 --> 42:01.354
- The infamous Asset.
- Yeah.

42:01.354 --> 42:04.482
The only thing Mathilde
La Fleur ever cared for.

42:04.482 --> 42:08.987
Her entire life revolves
around its protection,

42:08.987 --> 42:11.740
which is why you must help me
destroy it.

42:11.740 --> 42:13.742
[chuckles softly]
I--I don't--

42:13.742 --> 42:15.326
I don't understand
why you need my help.

42:15.326 --> 42:16.661
Have you tried a hammer?

42:16.661 --> 42:18.872
I have literally tried everything.

42:18.872 --> 42:20.707
This is no ordinary bowl.

42:20.707 --> 42:25.003
Because it's the Holy Grail.

42:25.003 --> 42:27.047
The physics lab
at this university

42:27.047 --> 42:30.175
has a Hercules Laser, right?

42:30.175 --> 42:31.926
<i>Oui.</i>

42:31.926 --> 42:36.931
We fire the laser
at the Asset.

42:36.931 --> 42:40.143
If it makes so much
as a scratch,

42:40.143 --> 42:42.854
you will never see me again.

42:42.854 --> 42:47.442
But if the bowl stays intact,

42:47.442 --> 42:52.405
you must vow
to help me destroy the Grail.

42:52.405 --> 42:55.325
Dear girl, that laser

42:55.325 --> 42:59.371
is going to burn a hole
through your bowl.

42:59.371 --> 43:00.747
Then vow.

43:02.457 --> 43:04.417
[scoffs]

43:06.920 --> 43:09.506
Sure. All right, why not?

43:09.506 --> 43:14.552
I vow to help you destroy
the Holy Grail.

43:14.552 --> 43:19.015
Whatever it takes.

43:19.808 --> 43:22.602
Whatever it takes.

43:22.602 --> 43:25.563
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

43:25.563 --> 43:27.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:27.691 --> 43:29.484
Then let us begin.

43:29.484 --> 43:36.449
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:41.955 --> 43:45.959
[laser whirring]

43:45.959 --> 43:48.837
Goggles on.

43:49.963 --> 43:53.133
[whirring]

43:58.013 --> 44:00.932
[laser zapping]

44:00.932 --> 44:07.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:09.733 --> 44:12.819
[laser powering down]

44:24.289 --> 44:25.999
[scoffs]

44:27.959 --> 44:31.004
What the shit?

44:38.011 --> 44:40.180
Right. Uh, here we are.

44:40.180 --> 44:42.349
This will be your room.

44:46.311 --> 44:48.480
You have a thing with cats.

44:50.231 --> 44:52.692
No, No, I don't have a thing
for cats, actually.

44:52.692 --> 44:55.070
My-- my colleagues,
they think it's hilarious

44:55.070 --> 44:57.364
to gift me, uh, feline-themed--

44:57.364 --> 44:59.449
[cat meows]

44:59.449 --> 45:00.492
Ah.

45:00.492 --> 45:02.702
And that's Apollo,

45:02.702 --> 45:04.746
who was also a gift.

45:04.746 --> 45:06.915
That reminds me.

45:09.209 --> 45:12.379
These were given to me
after the commercial.

45:12.379 --> 45:15.715
They're not my size,
but perhaps they fit you.

45:15.715 --> 45:16.841
Oh.

45:16.841 --> 45:19.052
Um...

45:22.972 --> 45:24.724
Look, Clara, I--

45:24.724 --> 45:28.103
I've--I've made it this far
in my professional life

45:28.103 --> 45:32.607
without being hindered
by, um, attachments.

45:33.858 --> 45:36.194
By family.

45:36.194 --> 45:38.530
And I have no intention
of breaking stride now.

45:38.530 --> 45:42.325
I invited you to stay purely
out of academic curiosity

45:42.325 --> 45:46.454
and the chance
for scientific exploration,

45:46.454 --> 45:48.081
nothing more.

45:48.081 --> 45:49.499
Of course.

45:49.499 --> 45:50.750
Me too.

45:50.750 --> 45:53.712
I only sought you out
as a means to an end,

45:53.712 --> 45:55.714
to help destroy the Grail.

45:55.714 --> 46:00.593
This is a strictly
professional partnership,

46:00.593 --> 46:02.262
nothing more.

46:02.262 --> 46:04.514
- Well, good. Good.
- Okay.

46:04.514 --> 46:07.475
<i>[soft music]</i>

46:07.475 --> 46:09.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:09.310 --> 46:11.604
Thanks--thank you very much
for the trainers.

46:11.604 --> 46:15.483
Um, actually, I've been meaning
to get myself a pair.

46:15.483 --> 46:17.235
Uh, um...

46:17.235 --> 46:19.404
maybe do not wear them
in public.

46:19.404 --> 46:21.656
There is an evil priest
out to get me,

46:21.656 --> 46:24.367
and he will recognize
those shoes.

46:24.367 --> 46:28.038
<i>Yeah, no shit
he'd recognize the shoes.</i>

46:28.038 --> 46:29.289
<i>They must have been
given away</i>

46:29.289 --> 46:31.249
<i>when I was presumed dead.</i>

46:31.249 --> 46:33.001
Yes, you mentioned
that the Vatican

46:33.001 --> 46:34.961
might be hunting you down.

46:34.961 --> 46:36.713
Do you have a plan for that?

46:39.341 --> 46:41.801
I stole a copy
of the commercial,

46:41.801 --> 46:44.262
and...

46:44.262 --> 46:47.640
I will send it
to that asshole as a warning.

46:47.640 --> 46:50.310
I just need to add
a little something of my own.

46:53.313 --> 46:55.732
Does that camcorder work?

46:55.732 --> 46:57.817
<i>That's when she recorded
the video.</i>

46:57.817 --> 46:59.361
<i>If you try to find me,</i>

46:59.361 --> 47:02.280
<i>or if I so much catch
a whiff of you...</i>

47:02.280 --> 47:04.866
Well, we may have engaged

47:04.866 --> 47:08.161
in some light blackmail.

47:08.161 --> 47:11.206
And did you destroy
the Grail?

47:13.249 --> 47:16.044
We certainly made
every attempt.

47:16.044 --> 47:20.882
We tried a pneumatic drill,
extreme heat, extreme cold,

47:20.882 --> 47:22.634
cold then hot, hot then cold.

47:22.634 --> 47:27.180
We threw it under a stampede
of elephants in Kenya.

47:27.180 --> 47:28.890
But nothing worked.

47:28.890 --> 47:31.267
Wow. That's a--that's a lot.

47:31.267 --> 47:33.603
How long did you do this for?

47:36.022 --> 47:37.691
Ten years.

47:37.691 --> 47:41.403
You traveled the world
with your daughter for years.

47:41.403 --> 47:44.364
While I still had
my academic posting,

47:44.364 --> 47:47.033
Clara and I would get together
once a month

47:47.033 --> 47:49.077
to test a new theory.

47:49.077 --> 47:52.080
I was just honoring my vow.

47:52.080 --> 47:53.331
So while
you and Clara were out

47:53.331 --> 47:55.834
doing your scientific expeditions,

47:55.834 --> 47:57.877
what was up
with the Articles of Care?

47:57.877 --> 48:00.422
Oh. Well, most of them,

48:00.422 --> 48:02.966
complete bollocks
and utter superstition,

48:02.966 --> 48:04.718
but, actually, except for one.

48:04.718 --> 48:07.220
Turns out the Grail did need
to be on the move.

48:07.220 --> 48:11.683
Otherwise, it would emit
the foulest odor.

48:11.683 --> 48:14.227
What happened
at the end of ten years?

48:14.227 --> 48:17.897
Well, it all culminated
October 31st, 2001,

48:17.897 --> 48:21.735
NASA launching a rocket
in the California desert.

48:21.735 --> 48:24.362
<i>And since we hadn't tried
exposing the Grail</i>

48:24.362 --> 48:28.158
<i>to ignited rocketed fuel,
made the trip.</i>

48:28.158 --> 48:30.994
<i>But it failed,
like all the others.</i>

48:30.994 --> 48:35.331
<i>There was one item
in the Articles of Care</i>

48:35.331 --> 48:37.542
<i>we hadn't yet dismissed,</i>

48:37.542 --> 48:41.963
<i>the most important of
the Sisters' ridiculous rules.</i>

48:41.963 --> 48:44.007
I'm going to drink from it.

48:44.007 --> 48:45.383
What?

48:45.383 --> 48:49.512
"Thou shall not sip,"
the most sacred rule.

48:49.512 --> 48:51.097
Why?

48:51.097 --> 48:53.683
Because maybe sipping is
what destroys it.

48:53.683 --> 48:56.603
It is literally the only thing
we haven't tried.

48:56.603 --> 48:58.104
Well, no.

48:58.104 --> 49:00.231
What about the volcano?

49:00.231 --> 49:02.984
We could rent a place
on the Big Island,

49:02.984 --> 49:04.861
and you could learn to surf.

49:04.861 --> 49:07.781
And I could just snorkel.

49:07.781 --> 49:09.866
Do you want to destroy
the Asset or go on vacation?

49:09.866 --> 49:12.660
No, of course
I want to destroy it.

49:12.660 --> 49:17.332
I just--I just like
spending time with you.

49:17.332 --> 49:20.335
<i>[soft music]</i>

49:20.335 --> 49:22.879
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:22.879 --> 49:24.589
I'm doing it.

49:24.589 --> 49:26.925
Wait--wait.
And--and then what happens?

49:26.925 --> 49:29.469
You drink, and what?

49:29.469 --> 49:31.846
It just bursts
into a cloud of dust?

49:31.846 --> 49:33.848
That's magical bloody thinking, Clara.

49:33.848 --> 49:36.810
You made a vow...

49:36.810 --> 49:38.687
to help me destroy it.

49:38.687 --> 49:45.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:46.945 --> 49:48.279
All right.

49:48.279 --> 49:50.615
But I'm gonna drink from it.

49:50.615 --> 49:52.283
No.

49:52.283 --> 49:54.160
Absolutely not.

49:54.160 --> 49:55.954
That was my idea.

49:55.954 --> 49:59.708
Yes, and given
the potential consequences,

49:59.708 --> 50:01.001
a dangerous one.

50:01.001 --> 50:02.419
[chuckles softly]

50:02.419 --> 50:05.839
You think it will kill me.

50:05.839 --> 50:08.508
Now who is doing the magical
bloody thinking, huh?

50:08.508 --> 50:10.135
Oh, come on, Clara.

50:10.135 --> 50:11.511
You're just as scared as I am,

50:11.511 --> 50:14.264
or you'd have sipped from it
years ago.

50:14.264 --> 50:16.266
No.

50:16.266 --> 50:19.686
I'm not scared.

50:19.686 --> 50:22.689
I just didn't want
to do it alone.

50:22.689 --> 50:28.319
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:28.319 --> 50:31.489
Okay.
[speaking French]

50:31.489 --> 50:33.158
Rock, paper, scissors.

50:33.158 --> 50:34.868
- Oh.
- One throw, winner drinks.

50:34.868 --> 50:38.580
And I will tell you in advance,
I'm throwing rock.

50:39.998 --> 50:42.459
But then all I have to do is
throw paper, and I win.

50:42.459 --> 50:43.793
Yeah, that's correct,

50:43.793 --> 50:45.920
because I am
definitely throwing rock.

50:45.920 --> 50:48.465
Wait, so do you want me
to drink from it?

50:48.465 --> 50:51.593
Because, you know, I will.

50:53.261 --> 50:55.555
I want you to do

50:55.555 --> 50:59.059
whatever you feel you have to

50:59.059 --> 51:00.560
in response to my rock.

51:00.560 --> 51:02.562
Yeah, yeah.
This is hurting my head.

51:02.562 --> 51:04.647
Okay, enough. Hands up.

51:04.647 --> 51:05.732
Ready?

51:05.732 --> 51:07.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:07.442 --> 51:08.902
Rock, paper, scissors.

51:08.902 --> 51:11.071
Throw!

51:11.071 --> 51:14.157
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:14.157 --> 51:15.784
What the fuck did she throw?

51:18.411 --> 51:19.662
Scissors.

51:19.662 --> 51:22.957
<i>[Clara Luciani's "Les fleurs"]</i>

51:22.957 --> 51:25.919
<i>[soft, funky music]</i>

51:25.919 --> 51:32.926
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:32.926 --> 51:34.052
You lied.

51:37.597 --> 51:40.475
<i>[singing in French]</i>

51:40.475 --> 51:44.104
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:44.104 --> 51:47.148
To magical bloody thinking.

51:47.148 --> 51:54.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:06.209 --> 52:07.168
[chuckles]

52:07.168 --> 52:12.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:12.632 --> 52:16.136
Well, that was definitely
worth the try.

52:16.136 --> 52:18.179
[laughs]

52:18.179 --> 52:24.978
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:30.275 --> 52:33.319
<i>And that's when this look</i>

52:33.319 --> 52:34.946
<i>came over her eyes,</i>

52:34.946 --> 52:39.034
<i>a sense of complete peace and...</i>

52:39.034 --> 52:42.412
tranquility.

52:42.412 --> 52:43.955
I'd never seen it before.

52:43.955 --> 52:46.499
It was as if--

52:46.499 --> 52:48.293
it was as if
she went somewhere.

52:48.293 --> 52:52.714
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:52.714 --> 52:56.009
I know where she was.

52:56.009 --> 52:57.469
And who she was with.

52:57.469 --> 53:01.431
Well, wherever she was,
she came back...

53:01.431 --> 53:06.811
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:06.811 --> 53:10.065
<i>And she smiled at me.</i>

53:10.065 --> 53:12.233
<i>And she said...</i>

53:12.233 --> 53:14.194
Whatever it takes.

53:14.194 --> 53:18.531
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:18.531 --> 53:22.118
[onlookers screaming]

53:25.080 --> 53:27.332
Her head exploded?

53:27.332 --> 53:28.833
Oh, Wiley, don't.
Just, don't.

53:28.833 --> 53:31.044
- Oh, my God!
- Wiley, don't.

53:31.044 --> 53:32.170
Wait, wait. Hold on.

53:32.170 --> 53:33.338
You lied to us, man.

53:33.338 --> 53:35.590
You said that
Clara was--was here.

53:38.218 --> 53:41.805
Not here.

53:41.805 --> 53:43.348
Here.

53:43.348 --> 53:46.351
<i>[intriguing music]</i>

53:46.351 --> 53:48.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:48.228 --> 53:50.897
And here.

53:50.897 --> 53:51.773
What?

53:51.773 --> 53:55.610
The moment that Clara died,

53:55.610 --> 54:00.490
I knew I had to get her liver
inside someone else.

54:03.451 --> 54:05.412
You see that cat?

54:05.412 --> 54:06.746
[cat meows]

54:06.746 --> 54:11.042
He's actually 35 years old.

54:11.042 --> 54:14.504
One day,
during our experiments,

54:14.504 --> 54:17.424
the Grail was left unattended
in my lab,

54:17.424 --> 54:21.511
and a mouse accidentally drank
from it.

54:21.511 --> 54:23.805
The mouse died.

54:23.805 --> 54:27.434
And then Apollo ate the mouse.

54:27.434 --> 54:29.269
The cat was absolutely fine.

54:29.269 --> 54:32.897
Subsequent bloodwork revealed
his organs to be

54:32.897 --> 54:37.527
totally pristine,
no damage whatsoever.

54:37.527 --> 54:39.571
What the fuck
are you talking about?

54:39.571 --> 54:41.948
Well, I had a theory
that the Grail itself

54:41.948 --> 54:44.784
had a microtoxin
baked into its finish,

54:44.784 --> 54:46.953
and perhaps that's what causes
the smell.

54:46.953 --> 54:49.831
Whatever it is,
it killed the mouse.

54:49.831 --> 54:51.916
But when Apollo ate that mouse,

54:51.916 --> 54:56.629
he developed an immunity,
like a vaccine effect.

54:56.629 --> 54:58.882
So after Clara died,
the only way to pass on

54:58.882 --> 55:02.969
any potential immunity was
an organ transplant.

55:02.969 --> 55:06.848
And the most
detoxifying organ is?

55:06.848 --> 55:08.975
- [softly] Shit.
- The liver.

55:08.975 --> 55:10.018
Yes.

55:10.018 --> 55:12.812
So whoever received
Clara's liver

55:12.812 --> 55:16.274
could theoretically drink
from the Grail.

55:16.274 --> 55:18.985
They would not only be immune
to its toxic effects

55:18.985 --> 55:22.530
but quite possibly
able to counteract them.

55:22.530 --> 55:25.158
And, as Clara
originally theorized,

55:25.158 --> 55:28.119
so destroy the Grail.

55:28.119 --> 55:31.790
- [softly] Holy...
- [mumbling]

55:31.790 --> 55:36.252
But when I saw you two,
you were just, um...

55:36.252 --> 55:38.838
you were children.

55:38.838 --> 55:40.757
You were there
at the hospital.

55:40.757 --> 55:44.219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:44.219 --> 55:45.345
What's your name?

55:45.345 --> 55:46.721
Lizzie.

55:46.721 --> 55:47.889
What's yours?

55:47.889 --> 55:50.517
Wiley.

55:50.517 --> 55:51.726
<i>I realized, in that moment,</i>

55:51.726 --> 55:54.437
<i>my obsession was too great,</i>

55:54.437 --> 55:58.775
<i>and to see it through
might well put others at risk.</i>

55:58.775 --> 56:01.778
<i>So if I couldn't destroy
the Grail,</i>

56:01.778 --> 56:04.906
<i>well, then,
I had to get rid of it.</i>

56:07.575 --> 56:09.661
It had to be in constant motion

56:09.661 --> 56:11.121
because of the smell.

56:11.121 --> 56:14.708
Now, luckily,
I knew some marine biologists

56:14.708 --> 56:16.376
who owed me a favor.

56:16.376 --> 56:19.212
And they took me out
on their research vessel,

56:19.212 --> 56:23.216
and I fed the Grail...

56:23.216 --> 56:26.219
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

56:26.219 --> 56:29.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56:29.139 --> 56:32.642
To a sperm whale.

56:32.642 --> 56:35.145
Did you say a whale?

56:35.145 --> 56:36.396
Yes.

56:36.396 --> 56:38.314
Yes, I did.

56:38.314 --> 56:41.943
Unfortunately,
after ingesting the relic,

56:41.943 --> 56:44.571
the whale went
a little bit berserk,

56:44.571 --> 56:47.657
and it destroyed our ship.

56:47.657 --> 56:52.412
That is how Apollo and I
ended up here

56:52.412 --> 56:55.790
on this island.

56:55.790 --> 56:59.711
The longer we stayed here,
I found,

56:59.711 --> 57:03.089
the less I thought about
destroying the Holy Grail

57:03.089 --> 57:06.426
until eventually,

57:06.426 --> 57:08.595
<i>I brought about my own rescue,</i>

57:08.595 --> 57:12.807
<i>after which I was introduced
to the Algorithm.</i>

57:12.807 --> 57:16.311
<i>She said I could ask Her
whatever I wanted.</i>

57:16.311 --> 57:18.438
And I knew
as soon as she proposed it

57:18.438 --> 57:20.065
that I was still obsessed,

57:20.065 --> 57:22.776
that my--my compulsion
to test the theory

57:22.776 --> 57:23.985
was as strong as ever

57:23.985 --> 57:26.738
because I asked her
for the whereabouts

57:26.738 --> 57:29.366
of Elizabeth Abbott
and Preston Wiley.

57:29.366 --> 57:32.827
I had to fight the urge
to seek you out.

57:32.827 --> 57:36.539
The only way
to guarantee your safety

57:36.539 --> 57:40.460
<i>would be for me to return
to this island forever.</i>

57:40.460 --> 57:42.379
But now,

57:42.379 --> 57:46.257
you two have found me
by your own volition.

57:46.257 --> 57:49.302
And whether that's fate
or coincidence

57:49.302 --> 57:50.887
or the Algorithm,

57:50.887 --> 57:52.931
I--I haven't got a clue.

57:52.931 --> 57:54.557
But all I do know is,

57:54.557 --> 57:58.895
it's a goddamned sign.

57:58.895 --> 58:02.857
Now, that whale has
a tracking device on it.

58:02.857 --> 58:04.442
We can find it,

58:04.442 --> 58:08.822
and I can, at last,
destroy the Holy Grail.

58:08.822 --> 58:12.784
So you want us
to get the Holy Grail

58:12.784 --> 58:15.578
out of a fucking whale

58:15.578 --> 58:18.248
so one of us can drink from it

58:18.248 --> 58:21.418
and maybe get
our heads exploded, hmm?

58:24.087 --> 58:27.298
That's about the size of it, yeah.

58:27.298 --> 58:28.550
[scoffs]

58:28.550 --> 58:32.512
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

58:32.512 --> 58:34.723
[scoffs forcefully]

58:34.723 --> 58:36.141
Lizzie.

58:36.141 --> 58:37.767
Come on.

58:37.767 --> 58:39.978
What do you say?

58:39.978 --> 58:42.397
That's crazy.

58:42.397 --> 58:44.691
What do you say?

58:44.691 --> 58:47.402
No. No, no.

58:47.402 --> 58:48.653
No, no.

58:48.653 --> 58:50.572
What do you say?

58:50.572 --> 58:53.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

58:53.700 --> 58:56.661
<i>[singing in French]</i>

58:56.661 --> 59:03.835
<i>♪ ♪</i>

59:08.757 --> 59:10.633
Whatever it takes.

59:10.633 --> 59:13.595
<i>[singing in French]</i>

59:13.595 --> 59:20.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>
